<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>IELTS Test</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.2/css/all.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/Home.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/IELTS/IELTSExam.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('../../partials/Header') %>
  <div class="page-container">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero-section">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>IELTS Test</h1>
        <div class="breadcrumb">
          <a href="#">Home</a> / <a href="#">IELTS Exam</a> / <span>IELTS Test</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="main-content">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <!-- Left Content (Text) -->
        <div class="content-left">
          <!-- What is IELTS? -->
          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>What is the IELTS™ Test?</h2>
            <p>The International English Language Testing System (IELTS) is designed to assess the language ability of candidates who need to study or work where English is the language of communication and instruction. It is a compulsory exam for admission into universities and training programs in the UK, Australia, New Zealand, and Canada. Professional bodies, government agencies, and immigration authorities also recognize the test.</p>
          </section>

          <!-- Why IELTS is Required -->
          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Why the IELTS Exam is Required</h2>
            <p>In English-speaking countries such as Australia, the UK, New Zealand, the USA, and Canada, the IELTS exam is necessary for both academic and immigration purposes. For candidates seeking visas from both inside and outside the UK, the IELTS exam is the only English Language Test approved by the UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI).</p>
          </section>

          <!-- Top Countries Accepting IELTS -->
          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Top Countries Accepting IELTS Score</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>United Kingdom (UK)</li>
              <li>United States of America (USA)</li>
              <li>Australia</li>
              <li>Canada</li>
              <li>Germany</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- IELTS Exam Pattern -->
          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>IELTS Exam Pattern & Syllabus</h2>
            <div class="highlight-box">
              <table>
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>IELTS Test Module</th>
                    <th>Time Duration</th>
                    <th>Brief Description</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Listening</td>
                    <td>30 minutes</td>
                    <td>4 sections, 40 items</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Writing</td>
                    <td>60 minutes</td>
                    <td>2 writing tasks</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Reading</td>
                    <td>60 minutes</td>
                    <td>3 sections, 40 questions</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Speaking</td>
                    <td>11 – 14 minutes</td>
                    <td>3 part one-on-one conversation</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- IELTS Exam Fees -->
          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>IELTS Exam Fees</h2>
            <p>In India, the IELTS exam fee is Rs. 16,250. You will get a refund of less than a 25% administrative fee if you cancel your IELTS registration more than five weeks prior to the test date. You won’t get a refund if you cancel your IELTS exam less than five weeks before the test date.</p>
          </section>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Content (Form) -->
        <div class="content-right">
            <form class="enquiry-form" id="enquiryForm" action="/submit-ieltsTest" method="POST">
                <h3>Planning to study abroad?</h3>
                <p>Get free 1-on-1 counselling with our experts</p>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="text" id="firstName" name="firstName" required>
                    <label for="firstName">First Name</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="text" id="lastName" name="lastName" required>
                    <label for="lastName">Last Name</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                    <label for="email">Email</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="tel" id="mobile" name="mobile" pattern="[0-9]{10}" required>
                    <label for="mobile">Mobile No. (10 digits)</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <select id="program" name="program" required>
                        <option value="">Select Program</option>
                        <option value="GMAT">GMAT</option>
                        <option value="GRE">GRE</option>
                        <option value="IELTS">IELTS</option>
                    </select>
                    <label for="program">Select Program</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <select id="mode" name="mode" required>
                        <option value="">Select Mode</option>
                        <option value="Classroom">Classroom Coaching</option>
                        <option value="Online">Online Coaching</option>
                    </select>
                    <label for="mode">Select Mode</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="form-group">
                    <select id="city" name="city" required>
                        <option value="">Select City</option>
                        <option value="Noida">Noida</option>
                        <option value="Delhi">Delhi</option>
                        <option value="Gurgaon">Gurgaon</option>
                    </select>
                    <label for="city">Select City</label>
                </div>
    
                <div class="checkbox-group">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="authorize" name="authorize" required>
                    <label for="authorize">I authorize Scoreup - The Princeton Review to contact me even if my number is registered with DND to assist with my enquiry and get regular updates through SMS/Whatsapp.</label>
                </div>
    
                <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Submit</button>
            </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>

  <!-- Back to Top Button -->
  <div class="back-to-top" onclick="scrollToTop()">&#8593;</div>

